    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="115"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/157</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-09">March 9,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Murray</hi>: I think Dr. Berle is right.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d115fn3">Attached to Mr. Murray’s memorandum, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra</hi>, is a handwritten notation by the Assistant Secretary of
                        State, Adolf A. Berle, Jr., dated March 9, as follows: “I think we should
                        promptly consider setting up diplomatic representation at Addis
                        Ababa”.</note> My thought would be that if we have some appropriate officer
                    who can be spared in the Near East we could reopen our mission in Addis Ababa
                    with a Chargé d’Affaires.</p>
                <p>Please consult Dr. Berle and Mr. Shaw<note n="4" xml:id="d115fn4">G. Howland
                        Shaw, Assistant Secretary of State.</note> and let me have your joint
                    recommendations so that I may take the matter up with the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
